label.value: Locally Advanced Unresectable Ovarian High Grade Serous Adenocarcinoma

value.value: An ovarian high-grade serous adenocarcinoma that has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes and is not amenable to surgical resection.

label.value: Locally Advanced Unresectable Fallopian Tube Carcinoma

value.value: Fallopian tube carcinoma that has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes and is not amenable to surgical resection.
This gene plays a role in the formation of N1-methyladenine at position 58 (m1A58) in initiator methionyl-tRNA.

Human TRMT61A wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 14q32.33 and is approximately 8 kb in length. This allele, which encodes tRNA (adenine(58)-N(1))-methyltransferase catalytic subunit TRMT61A protein, is involved in the methylation of tRNA and mRNA.
tRNA (adenine(58)-N(1))-methyltransferase catalytic subunit TRMT61A (289 aa, ~31 kDa) is encoded by the human TRMT61A gene. This protein plays a role in N1-adenine methylation in tRNA and mRNA.

label.value: Locally Advanced Unresectable HER2-Negative Breast Carcinoma

value.value: A HER2-negative breast adenocarcinoma that has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes and is not amenable to surgical resection.

label.value: Locally Advanced Hormone Receptor-Positive Breast Carcinoma

value.value: Hormone receptor-positive breast carcinoma that has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes.

A nonsteroidal 2-phenyl indole and a selective estrogen receptor modulator (SERM) with potential antineoplastic activity. Pipendoxifene antagonizes binding of estradiol to estrogen receptor alpha (ER alpha), thereby inhibiting ER alpha-mediated gene expression, interfering with estrogen activity and inhibiting estrogen-stimulated growth in estrogen-dependent breast cancer. In addition, this agent also exerts intrinsic estrogenic activity depending on the tissue types.
The study of the psychological and behavioral changes that occur in an organism between birth and old age.

label.value: Locally Advanced Unresectable Hormone Receptor-Positive Breast Carcinoma

value.value: Hormone receptor-positive breast carcinoma that has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes and is not amenable to surgical resection.

A cancer-associated fibroblast characterized by novel expression of major histocompatibility complex class II molecules, which are capable of antigen presentation. These cells may mediate immune evasion.

label.value: Locally Advanced Unresectable Triple-Negative Breast Carcinoma

value.value: Triple-negative breast carcinoma that has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes and is not amenable to surgical resection.
A person engaged to care for one or more children when their parents or guardians are not home.
A morphologic finding indicating the presence of extracellular mucin in a tumor sample.

label.value: Invasive Breast Lobular Carcinoma with Extracellular Mucin

value.value: A rare variant of invasive breast lobular carcinoma characterized by the presence of pools of extracellular mucin in which groups of floating lobular carcinoma cells are identified.
Endometrial carcinoma that has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes and is not amenable to surgical resection.
A nucleotide substitution at position 946 of the coding sequence of the MAP2K2 gene where guanine has been mutated to adenine.
A variation in the amino acid sequence for the dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase 1 protein.
A change in the amino acid residue at position 322 in the dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase 1 protein where glutamic acid has been replaced by lysine.
A molecular abnormality indicating rearrangement of the WWTR1 gene.

label.value: Locally Advanced Unresectable Lung Non-Small Cell Squamous Carcinoma

value.value: A non-small cell squamous carcinoma of the lung that has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes and is not amenable to surgical resection.
Cholangiocarcinoma that has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes and is not amenable to surgical resection.
Gallbladder carcinoma that has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes and is not amenable to surgical resection.
This gene is involved in androgen metabolism and steroidogenesis.

Human HSD17B11 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 4q22.1 and is approximately 55 kb in length. This allele, which encodes estradiol 17-beta-dehydrogenase 11 protein, plays a role in androgen metabolism.

Estradiol 17-beta-dehydrogenase 11 (300 aa, ~33 kDa) is encoded by the human HSD17B11 gene. This protein is involved in the conversion of 5-alpha-androstane-3-alpha,17-beta-diol (3-alpha-diol) to androsterone.
This gene plays a role in proton-sensing and G-protein coupled receptor signaling.

Human GPR65 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 14q31.3 and is approximately 10 kb in length. This allele, which encodes psychosine receptor protein, is involved in binding to psychosine, glucosylsphingosine and sphingosylphosphorylcholine. Overexpression of this gene is associated with malignant lipid droplet accumulation and tumor progression.
Psychosine receptor (337 aa, ~39 kDa) is encoded by the human GPR65 gene. This protein plays a role in glycosphingolipid-dependent G-protein coupled receptor signaling.
A test perfomed to identify a disease or make a prediction of the course of the disease.
This gene is involved in odorant-dependent neuronal responses.
Human OR2H1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p22.1 and is approximately 7 kb in length. This allele, which encodes olfactory receptor 2H1 protein, plays a role in the sense of smell.
Olfactory receptor 2H1 (316 aa, ~35 kDa) is encoded by the human OR2H1 gene. This protein is involved in odorant-dependent G-protein-coupled receptor signaling.
Nicotine replacement therapies that use mouth spray, gum, lozenges, or inhaler. These provide a rapid increase in nicotine blood levels, but for a limited time.
Nicotine replacement therapy that use transdermal patches. These provide a sustained nicotine delivery over 24 hours.
This gene plays a role in the regulation of genes involved in cell differentiation.

Human GLIS1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1p32.3 and is approximately 233 kb in length. This allele, which encodes zinc finger protein GLIS1, is involved in the maintenance of multipotent cells. A translocation t(1;2)(p32;q13) which fuses this gene and the PAX8 gene is associated with thyroid hyalinizing trabecular tumor (HTT).
Zinc finger protein GLIS1 (620 aa, ~66 kDa) is encoded by the human GLIS1 gene. This protein plays a role in the repression of cell lineage commitment.
This gene is involved in pancreatic beta cell development.
The study of the role of diet in the development of disease.

Human GLIS3 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 9p24.2 and is approximately 524 kb in length. This allele, which encodes zinc finger protein GLIS3, plays a role in repression and activation of transcription and the development of pancreatic beta cells. Mutation of the gene is associated with neonatal diabetes and congenital hypothyroidism (NDH) and  a translocation t(2;9)(q14.1;9p24.2) which fuses this gene and the PAX8 gene is associated with thyroid hyalinizing trabecular tumor (HTT).
Zinc finger protein GLIS3 (775 aa, ~84 kDa) is encoded by the human GLIS3 gene. This protein is involved in pancreatic beta cell development and the regulation of transcription.
A molecular abnormality indicating rearrangement of the GLIS1 gene.
A molecular abnormality indicating rearrangement of the GLIS3 gene.

A fusion gene that results from a chromosomal translocation t(1;2)(p32;q13) which fuses exon 2 of the PAX8 gene with exon 2 of the GLIS1 gene. This fusion is associated with thyroid hyalinizing trabecular tumor (HTT).

A fusion protein encoded by the PAX8/GLIS1 fusion gene. This protein is comprised of the first 8 N-terminal amino acids from paired box protein Pax-8 protein fused to the entire zinc finger protein GLIS1 protein, including the zinc-finger containing DNA-binding domain.

A fusion gene that results from a chromosomal translocation t(2;9)(q14.1;9p24.2) which fuses exon 2 of the PAX8 gene upstream of either exon 3 or 4 of the GLIS3 gene. This fusion is associated with thyroid hyalinizing trabecular tumor (HTT).

A fusion protein encoded by the PAX8/GLIS3 fusion gene. This protein is comprised of the first 8 N-terminal amino acids from paired box protein Pax-8 protein fused to most of the zinc finger protein GLIS3 protein, including the zinc-finger containing DNA-binding domain.
This gene is involved in the modulation of cell cycle progression, protein phosphorylation, cytokinesis and apoptosis.
